race.comment: Nearing D-day for BIG SISTER AVA (8), who has started favourite at two runs to date, both of which have been in stronger races than this. Most importantly, though, she gets to 2000m which should be right up her alley. STELLETTA (14) did her best work late and finished third last time over 1500m at Mornington, beaten 0.9 lengths. That was a sharp improvement on the first two runs and the extra trip suits with the added fitness under her belt. TUPAC (6) is a three-start maiden who finished sixth, beaten 1.5 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1600m at Ballarat. That was a stronger race than most of the rivals here come through. KISS'N DANCE (3) was dealt no favours at the barrier draw but 2000m third-up after an improved run last time looks perfect.
